<div class="content-data"><div id="list-content-mobile" class="hidden-md hidden-lg"></div><div class="lesson-tab" role="tabpanel"><ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist"><li role="presentation" class="active"><a href="#about" aria-controls="about" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Course details</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#transcript" aria-controls="transcript" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Transcript</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#pattern" aria-controls="pattern" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Pattern</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#diploma" aria-controls="transcript" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Diploma</a></li><li role="presentation"><a class="faq-tab blank" href="#faq" aria-controls="faq" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">FAQs</a></li></ul><div class="tab-content"><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane active" id="about"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><div class="demo-slider"><h4 class="text-center">Garments you can make using this technology:</h4><div id="amazingcarousel-container"><div id="amazingcarousel" style="display:none"><div class="amazingcarousel-list-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-list-wrapper"><ul class="amazingcarousel-list"><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2045.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2045.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2089.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2089.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2147.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2147.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li></ul></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>Features:</strong></p><p>The most distinguished feature of this corset is the scalloped edges in the neckline and the bottom.</p><p>There were several reasons, which motivated me to prepare this course:</p><p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;large number of orders for such corsets.</p><p>2. the unwillingness of the clients to adequately pay for the extra laborious work of making the scalloped corset. Therefore, in this course I will teach you a simple, an easy and yet a fast technique to sew the corset with scalloped edges and at the same times a technique that helps to achieve the desired result.</p><p>The use of my technique will turn the sewing of such complex corset into the budget option, which will be beneficial for you and your client!</p><p><strong>Where to use:</strong></p><ul><li>Perfect for sewing wedding dresses&nbsp;or evening garments;</li><li>Garments made with&nbsp;this technology are suitable for any body type and size;</li><li>Great for reshaping silhouettes and creating proportional forms.</li></ul><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;4h 30m</p></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-15-pinning-the-face-and-the-lining/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-15-pinning-the-face-and-the-lining/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-01-04T16:25:41+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2019-01-04T16:25:41+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2019"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 15. Pinning the face and the lining."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 15. Pinning the face and the lining."><meta itemprop="description" content="Before joining the lining with the face, it is necessary to cover the cup on the lining with padding polyester. There will be the scalloped neckline"><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Fantasy Corset"><meta itemprop="keywords" content="fantasy corset, video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><h1><strong>Tutorial 15. Pinning the face and the lining. </strong></h1><p><strong>Before joining the lining with the face, it is necessary to cover the cup on the lining with padding polyester. </strong></p><p><strong>There will be the scalloped neckline along the upper part of the cup, therefore, it is enough to cover the cup with padding polyester in 3 to 4 cm above the bust line.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I pin padding polyester in the empty spaces between bones. </strong>The excess of padding polyester can be cut off immediately.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image010.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image012.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image014.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I stitch padding polyester. I remind </strong>that stitching in the bottom of the cup is made along the outer side of the perimeter bone, then along the inner side of the armscye bone and in the upper part of the cup it is in 4 cm above the bust line bone.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image016.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>While joining the padding polyester and the cup together, I simultaneously sew the ribbon-loops, which are used for hanging a ready garment on the hangers. &nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image018.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image020.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image022.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image024.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image026.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image028.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image030.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image032.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image034.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image036.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>I remove pins and trim padding polyester close to the joining seam. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image038.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>The work on the lining is completed.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image040.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I start joining the face and the lining together to have a one-piece garment.</strong></p><p><strong>I place the face and the lining right sides together.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image042.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I pin the face and the lining, starting from the armpit, continuing on the back and along the lacing. The upper cut is untouched, it remains open. </strong></p><p><strong>I turn out the cups in the opposite direction for more accurate alignment of the face and the lining and for the convenience of work.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image044.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>During pinning the face is placed slightly over the lining, so the tension of the main fabric in the cups will be stronger.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image046.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image048.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image050.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image052.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image054.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image056.jpg" alt=""><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>I pin the second side of the corset. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image058.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image060.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image062.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image064.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image066.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image068.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image070.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Thus, the lining and the face of the corset are pinned together.</strong></p><p><strong>The dart made on the lining under the cup</strong> is redistributed between the top and the bottom of the corset.</p><p>So, this is absolutely normal if the face fabric goes beyond the lining in the neckline. I will cut the excess of this fabric in the course of work.</p><p>Thanks to this dart, a fold appears between the cups of the lining and the face, which completely eliminates such defect as a strongly protruding bust.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image072.jpg" alt=""></p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format.</p><p>To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose “<strong>PRINT IN ACTUAL SIZE</strong>“.</p><p>The pattern is divided to A4 paper sheets for home printer.</p> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/pattern-fantazia.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Fantasy Corset Pattern</a><br></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="diploma"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><p>In order to receive the Corset Academy graduation diploma you need to submit your graduation work.<br> Upload the photo of the garment that you made after completing the course.<br> I will personally review your work.<br> After the approval you will receive a personalized diploma to your email box, no longer than within 1 business day.</p><p class="text-right">Tatiana Kozorovitsky.</p><form id="diplomaForm"><h4>Your datails:</h4><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="firstname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter first name" required=""><p class="firstname error">Enter your first name</p></div><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="lastname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter last name" required=""><p class="lastname error">Enter your last name</p></div><h4>Choose a course:</h4><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option1" value="1"> <label for="option1"> <em>Wedding gowns design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option2" value="2"> <label for="option2"> <em>Evening dresses design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option3" value="3"> <label for="option3"> <em>Corsetry design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><p class="course error margin-10-bottom">Select course</p><div class="form-group"> <label class="uploadbutton"><div class="button">Choose file</div><div class="pull-left"><div class="input">No file selected</div></div> <input type="file" id="fileupload" name="files[]" data-url="https://corsetacademy.net/diploma/upload/"> </label><div id="progress" class="progress" style="display: none;"><div class="bar progress-bar progress-bar-warning progress-bar-striped active" role="progressbar" style="width: 0%;"></div></div> <input type="hidden" id="uploadDataUrl"><p class="upload error">Please upload photo of your work.</p><p>Max file size 2 Mb</p></div> <input type="hidden" id="userEmail" value="ngochuy.mmt@gmail.com"> <button id="submitDiploma" type="submit" class="btn btn-green-simple">Submit</button><h3 id="submitSpinner" class="text-center" style="display:none"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i></h3></form><h4 id="statusAnswer" class="text-center"></h4><div class="clearfix"></div><h3 class="get-pro text-center">The example of the diploma:</h3> <a href="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/diploma_example.png" class="wplightbox" title="Diploma Example"><div id="diploma_example"></div> </a></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="faq"><p class="text-center"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-pulse fa-3x"></i></p></div></div></div></div>

